Package entities

Class ActiveParking

java.lang.Object
entities.ActiveParking
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class ActiveParking extends Object implements Serializable
Represents an active parking record as stored in the database. This class contains details about a current parking session, including subscriber ID, entry time, expected exit time, parking spot, and whether the parking duration has been extended.

    • ActiveParking

      public ActiveParking(String parkingCode, int subscriberId, String entryDate, String entryTime, String expectedExitDate, String expectedExitTime, String parkingSpot, boolean extended)
      Constructs a new ActiveParking instance with the specified details.
      Parameters:
      parkingCode - Unique code identifying the parking session.
      subscriberId - The ID of the subscriber using the parking spot.
      entryDate - The entry date in format yyyy-MM-dd.
      entryTime - The entry time in format HH:mm.
      expectedExitDate - The expected exit date in format yyyy-MM-dd.
      expectedExitTime - The expected exit time in format HH:mm.
      parkingSpot - The number or identifier of the parking spot.
      extended - Whether the parking session has been extended.
